Song Clustering¶

In [8]:
# Importing the necessary libraries
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
In [9]:
# Selecting relevant audio features for clustering
audio_features = df[['danceability', 'energy', 'key', 'loudness', 'mode', 'speechiness', 
                     'acousticness', 'instrumentalness', 'liveness', 'valence', 'tempo']]
In [17]:
# Standardizing the features
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaled_audio_features = scaler.fit_transform(audio_features)
In [21]:
# Reducing dimensionality using PCA
pca = PCA(n_components=2)
reduced_features = pca.fit_transform(scaled_audio_features)
In [15]:
# Determining the optimal number of clusters using the Elbow method
inertia = []
for k in range(1, 11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42)
    kmeans.fit(scaled_audio_features)
    inertia.append(kmeans.inertia_)
